properties.areaDesc: Coastal waters from Sandy Hook to Manasquan Inlet NJ out 20 nm
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 8 at 12:40AM EST until February 8 at 1:00PM EST by NWS Mount Holly NJ
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Low Water Advisory, abnormally low water levels.
For the Small Craft Advisory, west winds 15 to 25 knots with
gusts up to 30 knots and seas 5 to 8 feet.

* WHERE...The coastal waters from Sandy Hook to Manasquan Inlet,
New Jersey.

* WHEN...For the Low Water Advisory, until 5:00 AM. For the Small
Craft Advisory, until 1:00 PM this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft. Below
normal water levels will result in hazardous navigating
conditions.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating a small
vessel, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 1 PM EST THIS AFTERNOON... ...LOW WATER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 AM EST EARLY THIS MORNING... ...GALE WARNING IS CANCELLED
